CommonFields.Publication: Journal of Polymer Science Part B: Polymer Physics
CommonFields.Title: Graphitic nanofillers in PMMA nanocomposites—An investigation of particle size and dispersion and their influence on nanocomposite properties
CommonFields.Author: Ramanathan, T.
Stankovich, S.
Dikin, D. A.
Liu, H.
Shen, H.
Nguyen, S. T.
Brinson, L. C.
CommonFields.Location: Department of Mechanical Engineering, Northwestern University, Evanston, Illinois‐60201

Mixing.Description: PMMA was dissolved in a minimum amount of THF (30 mL)
shear mixing applied in an ice-bath
dispersion dropped into vigorously stirred methanol to remove THF

ChooseParameter.Other: solid filtered through 10-micron PTFE filter paper

Drying-Evaporation.Description: filtered solid dried in vacuum oven to produce flakes

MoldingInfo.Description: dried flakes placed between two steel plates with 0.1-mm-thick spacers in a hydraulic hot-press

Cooling.Description: samples were cooled to room temperature after being hot-pressed

AcceleratingVoltage.description: 1-20 kV depending on different imaging purposes

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: temperature ramp of 3 C/min from 25 to 170 C

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Equipment: Solartron 1290 impedance analyzer with 1296 dielectric interface

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The measurements were performed from room temperature to 800C with a heating rate of 10 C/min in a flowing nitrogen atmosphere

SampleSize.description: 15 x 4.0 mm^2 strips for mechanical testing

SampleThickness.description: samples for XRD and SEM analysis as well as mechanical testing
